classes.name: PSDraw
classes.docstring:
Sets up printing to the given file. If ``fp`` is omitted,
``sys.stdout.buffer`` is assumed.

methods.name: begin_document
methods.docstring: Set up printing of a document. (Write PostScript DSC header.)

methods.name: setfont
methods.docstring:
Selects which font to use.

:param font: A PostScript font name
:param size: Size in points.

methods.name: line
methods.docstring:
Draws a line between the two points. Coordinates are given in
PostScript point coordinates (72 points per inch, (0, 0) is the lower
left corner of the page).

methods.name: rectangle
methods.docstring:
Draws a rectangle.

:param box: A tuple of four integers, specifying left, bottom, width and
   height.

methods.name: text
methods.docstring:
Draws text at the given position. You must use
:py:meth:`~PIL.PSDraw.PSDraw.setfont` before calling this method.

methods.name: image
methods.docstring: Draw a PIL image, centered in the given box.
